## Scenario 23 — deactivation doesn't touch order history

Not a new endpoint — this is Phase 2's PATCH /api/users/{id}/status
(deactivate) applied to a customer who already has orders from Phase 5,
proving ORD-014/ACC-007 hold once both phases coexist.

Request sequence:
```json
POST /api/orders                                    (Phase 5, Chen buys prod-0004)
PATCH /api/users/{chenId}/status  {"status":"DEACTIVATED"}   (Phase 2)
GET /api/orders/{chenOrderId}     Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
```

Response to the final GET — 200 OK, completely unchanged by the
deactivation in between:
```json
{
  "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002",
  "customerId": "cccccccc-cccc-4ccc-8ccc-cccccccccccc",
  "status": "PLACED",
  "totalAmount": "94.99",
  "items": [
    { "productId": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000004", "productName": "Trail Runner 2.0", "unitPrice": "94.99", "quantity": 1, "lineTotal": "94.99" }
  ],
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T14:30:00Z"
}
```

